name: Total DramaRama
overview: Some of the original "Total Drama" characters enter into an alternate universe where they are aged down from teenagers to toddlers.

episodes.name: Venthalla
episodes.overview: Owen has his super ball confiscated and locked up in Chef's office. Duncan, seeing an opportunity to get help escaping the daycare, leads an away team into the vents to recover Owen's ball.

episodes.name: Duck Duck Juice
episodes.overview: After daring each other to drink Chef's Pegasus Rainbow Latte, Izzy and Jude are jacked up like crazy and Duncan and Courtney take a road trip to try and replace the drink before Chef finds out it's gone.

episodes.name: Cluckwork Orange
episodes.overview: After befriending a chicken with a bad attitude at a petting zoo, Jude is followed back to school by the chicken. He defends the bird's behavior until he can defend it no longer.

episodes.name: Free Chili
episodes.overview: When Owen hides a walkie talkie inside his chili dog, Harold believes it's an alien here to destroy Earth.

episodes.name: The Date
episodes.overview: When Chef is happy he orders pizza for the kids, Owen & Jude get the idea to create a fake secret admirer for Chef.

episodes.name: Aquarium for a Dream
episodes.overview: Gwen tries to convince Chef to tell the class the truth about their pet goldfish.

episodes.name: Cuttin' Corners
episodes.overview: Duncan, Leshawna and Jude all want corner pieces of Izzy's Birthday Cake... but are they prepared to go to any length to get one?

episodes.name: Sharing is Caring
episodes.overview: Courtney refuses to share her valuable collectors-item toy with her classmates.

episodes.name: Ant We All Just Get Along
episodes.overview: Owen and Beth try to save an ant hill that Courtney and Leshawna want to destroy.

episodes.name: Germ Factory
episodes.overview: After seeing Leshawna enjoying a sick day at home with ice cream and TV, Duncan convinces the other kids to try and get sick too.

episodes.name: Cone in 60 Seconds
episodes.overview: After Owen gets ripped off at the ice cream truck, the kids unite to right that wrong.

episodes.name: The Bad Guy Busters
episodes.overview: Izzy wants to play a superhero game and is willing to do whatever it takes to get the others to see it through.

episodes.name: That's a Wrap
episodes.overview: Duncan goes on a mission to scare Courtney during a field trip to the museum.

episodes.name: Tiger Fail
episodes.overview: Gwen refuses to be pressured into choosing an ice cream flavor that she does not want.

episodes.name: A Ninjustice to Harold
episodes.overview: Harold's world is turned upside down when Beth becomes the class ninja.

episodes.name: Having the Timeout of Our Lives
episodes.overview: Owen forms a special bond with Duncan after having loads of fun with him during their timeouts.

episodes.name: Hic Hic Hooray
episodes.overview: Bridgette gets the hiccups and becomes desperate to get rid of them.

episodes.name: Bananas & Cheese
episodes.overview: Duncan is determined to stop the musical duo Bananas & Cheese from coming to the daycare.

episodes.name: Inglorious Toddlers
episodes.overview: Owen fears he's about to lose his BFF Noah to a gifted military school.

episodes.name: Not Without My Fudgy Lumps
episodes.overview: Noah tries to rescue the chocolates Owen forgot outside.

episodes.name: Paint That a Shame
episodes.overview: Leshawna creates a paint balloon fight to decide who gets to come with her to an amusement park.

episodes.name: Snots Landing
episodes.overview: Beth gets Courtney's diorama furniture stuck up her nose and Courtney needs it back before the diorama contest judge arrives.

episodes.name: Know it All
episodes.overview: Courtney must go all day without correcting her friends which is hard because they do everything wrong!

episodes.name: A Licking Time Bomb
episodes.overview: Owen and Noah unwittingly become cookie moguls and must hide the secret ingredient, which is Owen's spit from licking the sprinkles off the cookies.

episodes.name: From Badge to Worse
episodes.overview: In order to earn her final Girl Campers badge Courtney must earn Gwen's friendship.

episodes.name: Toys Will Be Toys
episodes.overview: Courtney becomes a toy tester but forgets that the most important thing is to have fun.

episodes.name: All Up in Your Drill
episodes.overview: Duncan stages a small coup to oust Courtney as their official class firefighter so that he can wear the shiny firefighter helmet - until he smells smoke in the classroom and begs her to take her job back.

episodes.name: Snow Way Out
episodes.overview: Owen wants everyone to love his new snowsuit and envy him, but it's just not working out that way.

episodes.name: Stay Goth, Poodle Girl, Stay Goth
episodes.overview: Gwen accidentally brings a pink stuffed pony she loves to daycare and spends the day denying it's hers.

episodes.name: Gum and Gummer
episodes.overview: Beth gets her gum stuck in Leshawna's hair and has to get it out - without Leshawna finding out it's there.

episodes.name: Invasion of the Booger Snatchers
episodes.overview: Harold believes that the picture day photographer is somehow turning the kids into well behaved zombies.

episodes.name: Wristy Business
episodes.overview: Beth and Leshawna try to one-up each other with fake injuries as they compete for the attention and sympathy of the other kids at daycare.

episodes.name: Melter Skelter
episodes.overview: When Chef tells Beth he won't buy the new super amazing toy she wants because they already have plenty to play with, she goes on a mission to get rid of their toys.

episodes.name: The Never Gwending Story
episodes.overview: When Chef loses the last page of the story-time book, Gwen takes over and creates a monster that all the kids start to believe in.

episodes.name: There Are No Hoppy Endings
episodes.overview: Chef struggles to maintain his sanity when the kids continue to blame a stuffed rabbit named Hoppy for everything they do wrong.

episodes.name: Too Much of a Goo'd Thing
episodes.overview: Beth refuses to believe that the adorable goo creature she's created out of slime is consuming the kids until she and Gwen are the only two left in class.

episodes.name: The Price of Advice
episodes.overview: After a paper origami fortune teller tells Izzy she's the world's best advice giver, she's determined to prove it.

episodes.name: Mother of All Cards
episodes.overview: Chef attempts to trick the kids into making his mother gifts after he forgets Mother's Day.

episodes.name: Duncan Disorderly
episodes.overview: Duncan escapes during a community walk only to discover he has to babysit Cody and Bridgette.

episodes.name: Soother or Later
episodes.overview: Duncan finally manages to break out only to realize he's forgotten his pacifier and needs to break back into the school to get it.

episodes.name: Camping is In Tents
episodes.overview: A class camping trip turns into a treasure hunt while Harold is determined to catch Bigfoot and keep everyone safe.

episodes.name: Mutt Ado About Owen
episodes.overview: After accidentally hypnotizing Owen into being a dog, Harold thinks he must reverse the hypnosis to avoid going to jail.

episodes.name: Simons Are Forever
episodes.overview: Duncan and Leshawna try to take advantage of Izzy's love for the game of Simon Says.

episodes.name: Stop! Hamster Time
episodes.overview: Owen takes over the job of caring for the class hamster and learns that he's evil.

episodes.name: Driving Miss Crazy
episodes.overview: Duncan leads Beth to believe she's broken his battery-powered bike and makes her chauffeur him around in a wagon for the day as punishment.

episodes.name: Weiner Takes All
episodes.overview: After forgetting to book a Hot Diggity Doggity Dog mascot on National Hotdog Day, Chef tries to pass off an Australian man dressed as a kangaroo as a substitute.

episodes.name: Apoca-lice Now
episodes.overview: When Chef brokers a truce with lice by selecting three kids to "host" them on their heads, Courtney instigates a kid vs. lice war.

episodes.name: Gnome More Mister Nice Guy
episodes.overview: When the daycare gets taken over by evil gnomes, Duncan finds himself on the wrong team.

episodes.name: Look Who's Clocking
episodes.overview: When Harold's warnings not to mess with the clock go ignored, the kids are forced to save themselves when Duncan tears a hole in the fabric of time.

episodes.name: Harold Swatter and the Goblet of Flies
episodes.overview: After finding what he believes to be a magic wand, Owen accidentally turns Harold into a housefly.

episodes.name: Stink. Stank. Stunk.
episodes.overview: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

episodes.name: Glove Glove Me Do
episodes.overview: Owen's newly found gloves make him great at everything. But this greatness comes at a high price.

episodes.name: Robo Teacher
episodes.overview: When a substitute teacher fills in for Chef, Duncan thinks it's going to be the best day ever. He's wrong.

episodes.name: The Tooth About Zombies
episodes.overview: When Gwen's favorite event, the Zombie March, falls on the same day as Noah's nightmare event, dental hygienist check up day, Gwen and Noah find a way to help each other out.

episodes.name: Lie-Ranosaurus Wrecked
episodes.overview: Owen pretends to be Izzy's pet dinosaur after leading her to believe she dug him up in the school playground.

episodes.name: An Egg-stremely Bad Idea
episodes.overview: Hoping to 'brighten her day', Izzy and Owen pimp out Gwen's egg chair. But when it ends up in a museum run by angry chickens, they must retrieve it before Gwen destroys the daycare in a temper tantrum of unspeakable darkness.

episodes.name: Exercising the Demons
episodes.overview: When a severe screen addiction turns the kids into lazy deadbeats, Chef brings in a professional to whip them into shape.

episodes.name: Pudding the Planet First
episodes.overview: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

episodes.name: Supply Mom
episodes.overview: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

episodes.name: Mooshy Phon Phons
episodes.overview: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

episodes.name: Student Becomes the Teacher
episodes.overview: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

episodes.name: Beth and the Beanstalk
episodes.overview: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

episodes.name: Pinata Regatta
episodes.overview: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

episodes.name: A Dame-gerous Game
episodes.overview: After Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen and Cody win a Hide & Seek competition, they're trapped on a private island by a jealous former champion and forced to play for their freedom.

episodes.name: Royal Flush
episodes.overview: When the other kids fear Harold has accidentally flushed himself down Chef's fancy new toilet, they travel into the sewer on a rescue mission. But will they find Harold before the mythical Alligator King traps them underground forever?

episodes.name: Total Eclipse of the F.
episodes.overview: Leshawna hatches a plan to extort the tooth fairy for money after destroying her loose tooth, only accidentally kidnaps the fairy instead.

episodes.name: Dissing Cousins
episodes.overview: It's International Cousins Day and Owen and Gwen are dreading the fact that their cousins Max and Ella are spending the day with them. And soon everyone else will understand why.

episodes.name: For a Few Duncans More
episodes.overview: While trying to photocopy on Chefâ€™s fancy new copier, Duncan accidentally makes an entire other Duncan.

episodes.name: He Who Wears the Clown
episodes.overview: After trying on the nose of a clown, Owen learns that this is how clowns are made and he is stuck as a clown until he can trick someone else into asking to try on the nose.

episodes.name: Us 'R' Toys
episodes.overview: When Chef brings in some old toys from his childhood he, Duncan and Gwen, each get magically sucked into one of the toys and need to find a way to get back into their own bodies.

episodes.name: Dream Worriers
episodes.overview: Izzy forgets the ending to her most amazing dream of all time and it continues until her brain is potato soup, so the kids travel into her mind to find out what happened.

episodes.name: Grody to the Maximum
episodes.overview: Cody gets cool clothing. That it's so cool that the kids don't even recognize him, so Cody jumps on the chance to leave his old life behind and become popular.

episodes.name: Wiggin' Out
episodes.overview: Bridgette donates her hair to a charity that makes wigs for hairless cats and now some classmates want to do the same. But their quest for perfect wig hair drives them to weird and dangerous lengths.

episodes.name: The Upside of Hunger
episodes.overview: Owen has a mishap while baking an upside-down cake and is transported to an upside-down world where he is forced to outwit himself in order to get his cake back.

episodes.name: Fire in the Hole
episodes.overview: Duncan cooks up a nuclear hot sauce to mess with Chef, but accidentally summons Terry Spice, King of the Underworld!

episodes.name: Ghoul Spirit
episodes.overview: Gwen rejects the friendship of a friendly ghost.

episodes.name: Duncan Carving
episodes.overview: Duncan takes advantage of a questionable Halloween legend to steal candy from his classmates.

episodes.name: Tu Ba Or Not Tu Ba
episodes.overview: The class tries to help Chef achieve his dream of joining the world's most famous tuba band, Tubalicious, only to regret it when they realize how much they'll miss him.

episodes.name: Dude Where's Macaw
episodes.overview: While trying to defend his elite gamer status, Chef uses an old cheat code that brings a dangerous avatar to life.

episodes.name: Way Back Wendel
episodes.overview: Courtney must deliberately lose a challenge or let the entire world go back in time.

episodes.name: Stingin' in the Rain
episodes.overview: When Chef gets locked outside in a storm, the kids mistakenly assume he's a robber and decide to protect the Daycare.

episodes.name: Cartoon Realism
episodes.overview: Gwen is frustrated by Beth's silly belief that cartoons are real, but they visit an animation studio and discovers the truth!

episodes.name: OWW
episodes.overview: When the kids discover Chef's past as a disgraced pro wrestler, they invite his old tag team partner to help put on a charity show. But his old partner doesn't comes for a reunion

episodes.name: Gobble Head
episodes.overview: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

episodes.name: Me, My Elf, and I
episodes.overview: Duncan tricks Chef into taking the class to the North Pole in order to remove his name from the naughty list.

episodes.name: Snow Country for Old Men
episodes.overview: In an attempt to win the holidays, Chef brings snowmen to life to entertain the kids, but a friendly snowman who brings joy isn't what it seems like.

episodes.name: Jelly Aches
episodes.overview: The school descends into chaos after getting a visit from Gazunga, the Jealousy Troll.

episodes.name: Simply Perfect
episodes.overview: When the kids are about to be subjected to school testing with no time to study, Courtney freaks and orders a Brainiac Ray from the back of a comic book that does not work as advertised.

episodes.name: Baby Brother Blues
episodes.overview: When Beth is told that the impending arrival of a baby brother is about to ruin her life, she runs away to find a new family.

episodes.name: Space Codyty
episodes.overview: Izzy who is convinced that Cody is an alien, embarks on a journey through space to take him back home.

episodes.name: Snack to the Future
episodes.overview: Owen wants his favorite treat, 'Jiggle Giggle', so bad that he's willing to use a time machine to get to snacktime quicker. But when he ends up stuck in the past, Owen must decide between getting home and getting fed.

episodes.name: The Gold and the Stickerful
episodes.overview: Courtney becomes infatuated with a new gold sticker incentive program that Chef introduces to the class.

episodes.name: Bad Seed
episodes.overview: Chef introduces the kids to agriculture by teaching them how to grow plants from seeds; however, when Izzy shows her seed too much love, it turns into a monster that terrorizes the class.

episodes.name: A Fish Called Leshawna
episodes.overview: After eating some mystery fish sticks, Leshawna achieves every little girl's dream and transforms into a mermaid!

episodes.name: Double Oh Beth
episodes.overview: With most of the class already gone for spring break, a nefarious villain infiltrates the school, With Beth trying to save the day.

episodes.name: Duncan Duty
episodes.overview: When Duncan realizes Chef is getting kids to tattle on him in return for chocolate milk, he sees an opportunity.

episodes.name: Encore'tney
episodes.overview: When Courtney turns to a magical datebook to help her achieve perfection, she's trapped in a never ending loop. It turns out that the datebook is taking advantage of Courtney and is being a bully to her.

episodes.name: Life of Pie
episodes.overview: When Izzy, Jude and Owen accidentally bring a pizza to life, they do everything they can to help him find a new purpose in life other than being eaten.

episodes.name: AbaracaDuncan
episodes.overview: When a magic trick goes sideways, Duncan makes a great escape and Harold becomes the target of a Sorcerer Hunt

episodes.name: Shock & AWW
episodes.overview: When Courtney gets the old, gross daycare carpet replaced with a new one, the resulting static electricity has unexpected consequences.

episodes.name: School District 9
episodes.overview: When a career predicting machine tells Owen he has no skills to offer the world, he decides to find a way to prove the machine wrong in the most Owen way possible.

episodes.name: The A-Bok-Bok-Bokalypse
episodes.overview: When chicken pox sweeps through the school, the kids visit the Chicken Queen to apologize for past misdeeds.

episodes.name: Gumbearable
episodes.overview: After accidentally swallowing a piece of gum, Owen has to protect his friends by jumping into the gum volcano.

episodes.name: Whack Mirror
episodes.overview: Chef warns Beth and Cody that making goofy faces into a mirror will cause them to get stuck that way. It turns out he was right, just not in the way any of them ever imagined.

episodes.name: Broken Back Kotter
episodes.overview: Chef gets nominated for the Daycare Professional of the Year award and the kids' will do whatever it takes to see him win.

episodes.name: Weekend at Buddy's
episodes.overview: After Cody's best friend doll breaks on Owen and Beth's watch, they put themselves in grave danger while trying to do the right thing.

episodes.name: MacArthur Park
episodes.overview: After losing countless jobs because of the kids, MacArthur shows up at the school seeking revenge.

episodes.name: Last Mom Standing
episodes.overview: When Chef's mom and Leshawna's grandmother drop their loved ones off at the same time, it kicks off a dangerous competition to prove who is the most caring mother-figure.

episodes.name: Carmageddon
episodes.overview: Duncan is rattled when Chef, tired of having his car destroyed, buys a new one that is completely indestructible.

episodes.name: Sugar & Spice & Lightning & Frights
episodes.overview: When two new kids show up at the daycare, Duncan and Leshawna take issue with not what makes them different, but what makes them similar to the newbies.

episodes.name: Breaking Bite
episodes.overview: Beth becomes the big dog on campus after she bites Duncan, but being the big dog is a dangerous thing, especially when she didn't actually bite anybody.

episodes.name: I Dream of Meanie
episodes.overview: When Cody keeps screaming in his sleep, Gwen and Duncan take a trip into his dreams to see what is scaring him.

episodes.name: Squirrels, Squirrels, Squirrels
episodes.overview: Courtney's attempt to make Chef a better teacher fails when a squirrel gets his hands on her mind-control device.

episodes.name: Say Hello to My Little Friends
episodes.overview: After telling the kids he will not miss them over a long weekend, Chef locks himself into the school and finds out he was very, very wrong.

episodes.name: WaterHose-Five
episodes.overview: The hottest day of the year and a broke air conditioner leads to a water battle of epic proportions to determine who controls the garden hose.

episodes.name: Cody the Barbarian
episodes.overview: Cody is set to inherit a video game empire from his long lost uncle, but only if he and his friends have what it takes to conquer a fantastical live action game.

episodes.name: TP2: Judgement Bidet
episodes.overview: When the city experiences a toilet paper shortage Beth and Harold investigates who stole all the town's toilet paper.

episodes.name: Dial B for Birder
episodes.overview: After Chef gets a parrot everyone is so distracted by its cuteness, until Harold reveals The Parrot's secret identity.

episodes.name: A Hole Lot of Trouble
episodes.overview: When rain derails an outside game of catch someone suggests they play it inside. This prompts Izzy to lead the group through her wildly imaginative worst-case scenario. It's an adventure so scary that the kids may never play again.

episodes.name: A Tall Tale
episodes.overview: After Owen's BFF, Noah, goes through a growth spurt, Owen fears losing his friend and takes drastic action.

episodes.name: Chews Wisely
episodes.overview: When the floor ends up covered in gum on the day of a big bubble blowing contest, someone decides  that she need to betray everyone to might help herself win by helping her friends get stuck to the floor.

episodes.name: A Dingo Ate My Duncan
episodes.overview: When all their classmates are replaced with well-behaved Australian doppelgangers in a school exchange program, Lightning and Cody start getting suspicious.

episodes.name: Erase Yer Head
episodes.overview: Gwen orders a personality modifying ray to tone her perky parents but decides to test it on the class first.

episodes.name: Teacher, Soldier, Chef, Spy
episodes.overview: When Beth, Duncan and Izzy break Chef's new VR helmet they have to recreate his game world to keep him from ever finding out the truth.

episodes.name: Thingameroo
episodes.overview: When a lack of motivation threatens to sink the kids' chances in the Sports Athletic Awards, they create the greatest mascot of all time to boost school spirit.

episodes.name: CodE.T.
episodes.overview: When Cody gets sick, the kids want to send a message back to his home planet in hopes that they can save him, but Courtney is not in favor of this plan.

episodes.name: Quiche It Goodbye
episodes.overview: When an evil conglomerate is threatening to take over Chef's favorite childhood restaurant, Owen rallies the kids to take them down.

episodes.name: Ice Guys Finish Last
episodes.overview: Chef brings a souvenir iceberg home from a trip to the South Pole and Duncan finds a prehistoric surprise inside.

episodes.name: Trousering Inferno
episodes.overview: The Bad Guy Busters must reunite to save Izzy after Harold uncovers her previous identity and leads a supervillain from her past right to her.

episodes.name: The Big Bangs Theory
episodes.overview: Chef forgets the password for his computer, and entering the wrong password will cause the school to blow up for the 100th time.

episodes.name: Gwen Scary, Gwen Lost
episodes.overview: Chef is devastated when he discovers his spooky Halloween pranks have never scared the kids; determined to finally get them, he agrees to hand over full control of his pranking to Gwen, whose plan turns out far spookier than Chef ever hoped.

episodes.name: Math Mad: Taffy Road
episodes.overview: A Harold from the Future convinces Courtney she must beat Courtney from The Future.

episodes.name: Bearly Edible
episodes.overview: Owen gets Cookies for The Year's Snack but he ate it so now he bought different cookies, but nobody likes it.

episodes.name: Not for the Paint of Heart
episodes.overview: When Izzy believes that Chef wants her to rise to the challenge of destroying the daycare with art, she gets some magic paint to bring all her creations to life.

episodes.name: Daycare of Rock
episodes.overview: After believing he's turned Chef to stone, Duncan sets his sights on ultimate chaos only to discover there's no joy in victory without an adversary.

episodes.name: Aches and Ladders
episodes.overview: When MacArthur has a bad fall in the school, the kids' recollections of the event are just as weird as they are.

episodes.name: The Tree Stooges Save Christmas
episodes.overview: The kids accidentally destroy Chef's decorated Christmas tree. Scared, this means they've ruined his Christmas, they go on an epic mission to replace his holiday treasures.

episodes.name: Cactus Makes Perfect
episodes.overview: Cody's friends become concerned when he forms a new friendship with a cactus.

episodes.name: Virtual Reality Bites
episodes.overview: When the school switches to virtual reality, Harold uses the opportunity to get the respect he feels he rightfully deserves.

episodes.name: The Opening Act
episodes.overview: After failing to open a jar Chef believes he's past his prime and entering his twilight years. This prompts Beth and the kids to dig up something from his youth to rejuvenate him. That something turns out to be a ventriloquist dummy named Sue.

episodes.name: Van Hogling
episodes.overview: Chef and the kids take a field trip to Sugar's farm but ignore all of Sugar's strict and boring farm rules that have dire consequences when Chef and the kids unleash a herd of ravenous Werehogs on a full moon.

episodes.name: Ticking Crime Bomb
episodes.overview: Leshawna and Izzy trick Owen into thinking he's destined to be a criminal mastermind, but when he leaves school to join the scariest gang in town, they have to mount a rescue attempt.

episodes.name: Be Claws I Love You, Shelley
